h$na clear-cut species classification.$\backslash$n4. Deciding whether intraspecific functional variability can be$\backslash$nconsidered as negligible - species being represented by mean trait$\backslash$nvalues -, or not - species being represented by multivariate trait$\backslash$ndistributions -, is an essential question for multiple ecological$\backslash$nissues. However, this decision cannot be generic, but will depend on the$\backslash$nstudied system and selected traits and species, as well as on study$\backslash$nobjectives.},
